2026 Regular Session
HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 81
BY REPRESENTATIVE FREIBERG
SCHOOLS/ENROLLMENT: Requests that the state Department of Education conduct a
study of options for public school systems facing declining enrollment
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the state Department of Education to study options for public school
3 systems facing declining enrollment and submit a written report of findings and
4 conclusions, including any recommendations for related legislation, to the House
5 Committee on Education and the Senate Committee on Education not later than
6 March 1, 2027.
7 WHEREAS, it has been reported that there are public school systems throughout the
8 state facing declining enrollment; and
9 WHEREAS, declining enrollment in public schools has been attributed to various
10 factors, including declining birth rates, the movement of families out of state, and enrollment
11 in nonpublic schools and home study programs; and
12 WHEREAS, declining enrollment can lead to budget cuts, school closures, and the
13 loss of jobs and programs; and
14 WHEREAS, it is important that Louisiana plan ahead in terms of addressing how
15 declining enrollment may affect the state's education landscape in the coming years.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
17 urge and request the state Department of Education to study options for public school
18 systems facing declining enrollment and submit a written report of findings and conclusions,
19 including any recommendations for related legislation, to the House Committee on
20 Education and the Senate Committee on Education not later than March 1, 2027.
